t: To the chief Musician, A Psalm for the sons of Korah.
O*p clap your hands, all ye people; shout unto God with the voice of triumph.
For*p the Lord*s most high is terrible; he is a great King over all the earth.
He*p shall subdue the people under us, and the nations under our feet.
He*p shall choose our inheritance for us, the excellency of Jacob whom he loved. Selah.
God*p is gone up with a shout, the Lord*s with the sound of a trumpet.
Sing*p praises to God, sing praises: sing praises unto our King, sing praises.
For*p God is the King of all the earth: sing ye praises with understanding.
God*p reigneth over the heathen: God sitteth upon the throne of his holiness.
The*p princes of the people are gathered together, even the people of the God of Abraham: for the shields of the earth belong unto God: he is greatly exalted.
